ASIAN CAPITALS: In 1776, during the reign of Timur Shah, the Durrani rulers moved their capital from Kandahar to this city
Kabul
The Durrani Pashtuns of the Afghan capital Kabul are usually bilingual in Pashto and Dari Persian.
1
Durrani () or Abdali () is the name of a chief Sarbani Pashtun tribal confederation in Afghanistan and Pakistan.